result.name: Cheung Hing Kee Shanghai Pan-fried Buns

reviews.text: Pretty nice and tasty snack before hopping on the mini bus home. Pasted it so many time but was always too full to try it. Today I had a little space so off I went and ordered a set of four. Service was fast. Prices are reasonable.  They have seating for you to eat in the air conditioned area. Overall pretty simple. They do have other offerings which I will try later. Dumplings were soupy as advertised. You have to be careful as the are hot and the can squirt all over your shirt, pants and shoe laces. I just love eating dumplings!
We LOVED THESE BUNS. We've tried several places and loved these. The black truffle option is so yummy. Family of 5 all agree. Give it a try
The best buns I've had the pleasure to taste in my life. Filled with hot juicy goodness. Take care not to burn your mouth! Slurp the juices from the inside before devouring the meaty fillings.
Forget about the poor environment when this might be the best pan fried bun in town. Just be aware of the hot juicy soup inside the bun when you bite it, don't burn your tongue.
$32 very juicy and intense pork flavor and crispy bottom shanghai style fried pork dumpling
